### Props Declaration

Props are custom attributes a component can receive from its parent. Declare them in the `props` option:

```vue
<script>
export default {
  props: ['title', 'likes']
}
</script>
```

### Prop Types

For better validation, declare props with types:

```vue
<script>
export default {
  props: {
    title: String,
    likes: Number,
    isPublished: Boolean,
    commentIds: Array,
    author: Object,
    callback: Function
  }
}
</script>
```

### Static vs Dynamic Props

**Static**: `<BlogPost title="My Journey" />`

**Dynamic**: `<BlogPost :title="post.title" />`

### One-Way Data Flow

Props follow a **one-way data flow**: parent → child. The child should NEVER directly mutate a prop. To modify, emit an event:

```vue
<script>
export default {
  props: ['modelValue'],
  emits: ['update:modelValue'],
  methods: {
    update() {
      this.$emit('update:modelValue', this.modelValue + 1)
    }
  }
}
</script>
```

### Prop Validation

```vue
<script>
export default {
  props: {
    title: {
      type: String,
      required: true,
      default: 'Default title',
      validator(value) {
        return value.length > 0
      }
    },
    count: {
      type: Number,
      default: 0
    }
  }
}
</script>
```

### Non-Prop Attributes

When a parent passes an attribute not declared as a prop, it falls through to the root element:

```vue
<!-- Parent -->
<MyButton class="large" />

<!-- Rendered child root -->
<button class="large">Click me</button>
```
